<p>For Fort Wayne's cold climate, dual-fuel systems or high-efficiency gas furnaces paired with 16-18 SEER air conditioning units provide optimal performance. Gas furnaces with 90-96% AFUE ratings excel during harsh winters, while heat pumps with backup electric or gas heating work effectively down to 25¬∞F. Since heating demands far exceed cooling needs in Fort Wayne, prioritize furnace efficiency over air conditioning SEER ratings. Variable-speed systems offer superior comfort control during the city's temperature fluctuations, maintaining consistent indoor conditions while reducing energy consumption. Cold-climate heat pumps rated for sub-zero operation are becoming increasingly popular, providing year-round efficiency even during Fort Wayne's coldest months.</p>

